-{"id":"beads_rust-o5mo","title":"Address "for now" deferred implementation markers","description":"PARENT TASK 7 of 7: The codebase has zero TODO/FIXME/HACK comments (remarkably clean), but three "for now" comments indicate deferred work that should be tracked as intentional technical debt:

(1) sync.rs:1270 — "For now, fail on conflicts. Future: interactive resolution or force flags." The sync merge currently hard-fails on any conflict. The comment explicitly calls out interactive conflict resolution as a planned feature. This is a significant usability gap for multi-agent workflows where JSONL merge conflicts are common.

(2) history.rs:443 — "Let us shell out to diff -u for now as it is standard on linux/mac." The history diff command shells out to the system diff binary. This breaks on Windows without WSL and contradicts the projects self-contained philosophy. A pure-Rust diff implementation (e.g., the similar or imara-diff crate) would eliminate the external dependency.

(3) dep.rs:903 — "For now, let us sort by ID to be deterministic, or fetch details. Priority sorting would require fetching issues." The dep list command sorts dependencies by ID string instead of by priority. For triage workflows, priority-sorted deps would be more useful but requires an extra DB query per dependency.

