 {"id":"beads_rust-o8d3","title":"Consolidate transaction and storage constants in sqlite.rs","description":"PARENT TASK 2 of 7: src/storage/sqlite.rs contains two identical function-local definitions of transaction retry parameters: MAX_RETRIES=5 and base_backoff_ms=10 at lines 218 and 615. These are defined inside with_connection_write_transaction() and with_write_transaction() respectively. Both implement the same exponential backoff retry logic for BEGIN IMMEDIATE. Having them as function-local consts means if one is tuned, the other is easily forgotten.

Additionally, WAL_CHECKPOINT_INTERVAL (50) and DEFAULT_BUSY_TIMEOUT_MS (30,000) are module-level constants but not user-configurable. DEPENDENCY_TRAVERSAL_MAX_DEPTH (500) is already a proper module-level const. The SQLite cache_size pragma -8000 (8MB) in schema.rs:441 is also an inline tuning parameter.

WHAT "DONE" LOOKS LIKE: MAX_RETRIES and BASE_BACKOFF_MS hoisted to module-level const items in sqlite.rs. Both transaction functions reference the shared constants. The schema.rs cache_size value gets a named const. No behavioral changes.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-03-25T03:02:12.748897326Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-25T04:03:25.465068349Z","closed_at":"2026-03-25T04:03:25.464606905Z","close_reason":"TX_MAX_RETRIES/TX_BASE_BACKOFF_MS hoisted, SQLITE_CACHE_SIZE_KB added. Both storage subtasks done.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["storage"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"beads_rust-o8d3","depends_on_id":"beads_rust-cl7v","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-25T03:33:36.148703442Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"beads_rust-o8d3","depends_on_id":"beads_rust-tifz","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-25T03:33:36.443997243Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
